caption: Good food and fast service 10/10
I order online 99% of the time and never had an issue to date. Yummy bagels and bagel sandwiches. Vanilla Hazelnut coffee is hot and tasty always. The team there does a great job.

I wanted to try their Farmhouse breakfast bagel but wanted to change the shmear to chive & onion. I wasn't able to make the customisation via their app so called into the store and tried to place the order that way, however, they don't take orders via the phone. So we asked them to make note of this change and placed the order via the app.  The Farmhouse bagel was super yummy! It's a fully loaded breakfast sandwich but totally worth it. I would recommend the chive and onion shmear - it's so good. Ordering via the app is pretty seamless.  Will be going back!
Very good service at 7:30 am. Few people in the store and everyone was masked. You can order ahead and pick up the order quickly from a table in the store.

Overall, great customer serive and food!

Great downtown breakfast joint.  It's hard to go wrong with anything they offer.  I tried several of their sandwiches and the coffee.  The sandwiches were made as-pictured (not the mushed soggy mess of fast food) and the coffee is hot and bold.  They carry a few varieties of Caribou Coffee, which is as good as or better than Starbucks.  Prices are generally high, but you'll get that with the good location and the higher quality food (you won't find them waffle tacos here).  Coffee prices are on par with Starbucks.  I guess that's just the going rate for bean water here.

The first time I was there I asked if their bagels were vegan and the worker said yes. Today I asked if there was any eggs or milk in their multigrain roll and the worker did not hesitate and said no, there isn’t. Her coworker proceeds to turn around and says, what was the question? Then says ALL the dough has eggs in it. This means I consumed eggs my first visit because a worker feigned confidence in her knowledge. This serves as a red flag to all vegans and people with food allergies.

I ordered a toasted bagel with butter and waiting about 10 minutes when I usually wait about 3 minutes. Turns out my bagel was sitting on the counter for 10 minutes while workers walked past and didn’t even let me know that my food was ready. An older gentleman working there even used the bathroom while my food sat on the counter. I would’ve grabbed it myself but I wasn’t aware anything was there due to where I was sitting. So I attempted to eat my bagel with butter cold. Clearly the workers don’t care. Sad.
